[00:07.60]Sunrise spills on an empty road
[00:11.87]Truck’s humming soft, miles to go
[00:16.14]Porch light fades, you wave goodbye
[00:20.42]I swallow hard, try not to cry
[00:24.69]Rearview mirror shows a house so small
[00:28.96]I carry it with me through it all
[00:33.23]Every mile, my heart aches slow
[00:37.51]Every goodbye feels harder to let go
[00:41.78]Warm hugs, your smile, your kiss
[00:46.05]These are the things I miss
[00:50.33]Little hands reachin’ for mine
[00:54.60]Soft whispers sayin’ “I love you” in time
[00:58.87]Rearview heart, lonely man
[01:03.15]But love’s my road back home again
[01:07.42]Hallway laughter, tiny feet
[01:11.69]Family games, spilled drinks and treats
[01:15.96]Sittin’ close, watchin’ the TV glow
[01:20.24]Cookin’, walkin’, everything I know
[01:24.51]Even the mess, the chores we share
[01:28.78]I leave behind pieces everywhere
[01:33.06]Quiet nights on this lonely road
[01:37.33]I hear your voices, lighten the load
[01:41.60]Warm hugs, your smile, your kiss
[01:45.88]These are the things I miss
[01:50.15]Little voices call my name
[01:54.42]I hold on tight, fightin’ the pain
[01:58.69]Rearview heart, lonely man
[02:02.97]But love’s still waitin’ where it began
[02:07.24]Church doors open Wednesday night
[02:11.51]Serve the sweet, clean the tables, turn out the light
[02:15.79]I work these miles to do what’s right
[02:20.06]God knows my heart, keeps me in sight
[02:24.33]Even when this road feels long
[02:28.61]Love and faith carry me along
[02:32.88]Warm hugs, your smile, your kiss
[02:37.15]Every reason I don’t quit
[02:41.43]Every mile, every prayer
[02:45.70]Every moment shows you care
[02:49.97]Rearview heart, lonely man
[02:54.24]But love’s my road back home again
[02:58.52]Yeah, love’s my road back home again…
